modules.description: This module defines predefined font sizes for use in image generation tasks. It provides values representing different font scales, such as tiny, small, medium, large, and giant. These font sizes can be directly used when rendering text onto images with varying size requirements.

This module provides tools for creating and manipulating images using the GD library, including loading PNG and JPEG files, determining color types, and rendering text with accurate bounding boxes. It supports dynamic image generation, text overlays with custom fonts, and precise measurement of text dimensions for layout purposes. The included child module supplies predefined font scales—like tiny, small, medium, large, and giant—that can be directly applied when drawing text onto images to accommodate different size requirements. These font values integrate seamlessly with the main module's text rendering operations, enabling consistent and scalable image generation workflows.
